                             Book List
                             ----------

() Belytschko, Ted, Wing Kam Liu, and Brian Moran, Nonlinear Finite Element for
        Continua and Structures, John Wiley & Sons, New York, 1997. $117.00.

() Chau, Pei Chi and Pagano Nicholas J., Elasticity: Tensor, Dyadic, and Engineering
        Approaches, Dover Publications Inc., New York, 1992.   $16.00

() Cantor, Henri, Differential Forms, Dover Publications Inc., Mineola, 2006.  $13.00

() Kuhnel, Wolfgang, Differential Geometry: Curves-Surfaces-Manifolds, 2nd Ed.,
        AMS, 2006.  $49.00

() Ferziger, J.H. and Peric, M., Computational Methods for Fluid Dynamics, 3rd rev. Ed.,
        Springer-Verlag, Berlin., 2002.

() Flanders, Harley, Differential Forms with Applications to the Physical Sciences,
        Dover Publications Inc., New York, 1989.  $13.00

() Fung, Y. C. and Pin Tong, Classical and Computational Solid Mechanics, World Scientific,
        River Edge, 2001.

() Gockenbach, Mark S., Understanding and Implementing the Finite Element Method,
        SIAM, Philadelphia, 2006.   $87.00

        (This book is good for the adaptive mesh refinement algorithms of Chapter 14)

() Graustein, William C., Differential Geometry, Dover Publications Inc., Mineola,
        2006.   $15.00

() Guggenheimer, Heinrich, Differential Geometry, Dover Publications Inc., New York,
        1977.   $15.00

() Hartshorne, Robin, Geometry: Euclid and Beyond, Springer, Berlin, 2000.  $44.50

        (This book describes hyperbolic geometry)

() Li, B. Q., Discontinuous Finite Elements in Fluid Dynamics and Heat Transfer, Springer,
        London, 2006.  $129.00

() Oden, J. T., Finite Elements of Nonlinear Continua, Dover, Mineola, 2000.  $23.95

() Oprea, John, Differential Geometry and its Applications, 2nd. Ed., Pearson Prentice-Hall,
        ???.  $111.00

        (Recommended by Rabin for Math 150 A) 

() Saad, Yousef, Iterative Methods for Sparse Linear Systems, 2nd Ed., SIAM,
        Philadelphia, 2003.   $95.00.

        (I think this is the book I wanted for its discussion of the Conjugate Gradient Method.)

() Schattschneider, D, and M. Emmer (Editors), M. C. Escher's Legacy: A Centinnial
        Celebration, 2nd. Ed., Springer, Berlin, 2005.  $35.00


